args:
News that reinforcements are being held up by
the enemy leaves Joachim floundering, but a
message from Noelle gives him the resolve to
act. He races to Kirsty's side, and together they
mount their counteroffensive.
All units, fall back! You can bet they'll be\nhot on our tails, so stay sharp!
You're really something else, Joachim.\nThis big of a difference in numbers\nand they STILL can't beat you!
Well, we haven't beat them either—\nand our troops are all at the end of their\nropes at this point.
The only reason we've held out this long\nis your guts and this manacaster that\nPrincess Chelle loaned us.
It outranges their bows by a long shot,\nand the way it roars when you fire it has\nthem shook. Wish we had a dozen more.
But once we can sign this deal and get one\nin the hands of every infantryman, Barthe's\ndays will be numbered!
It sounds like she still can't manufacture\nthem on that scale, sadly.

(Though that kind of scale is exactly what
the higher-ups are hoping for—and
whether that happens or not hinges on
this battle.)
R-reporting, sir! The right flank has\nsuffered heavy damage! They're being\npushed back!
So the wall's crumbling, and we don't\nhave the numbers to shore it up...\nTell them to hold on as best they can!
Noelle is coming, and the second she\narrives, the wind turns in our favor.
GYA! Noelle?! When did you...\nYou know what, forget it. Just please\ntell me you brought reinforcements!
The, um...the contingent from the\nHalidom won't make it in time.
Oh, what the hell! Why NOT?!
Th-the details are in this report\nI got from Kirsty!
Blocked routes... Enemy ambush...\nSounds like they're held up, all right.
Yes. The road's all torn up, so progress\nis slow... Er, and the enemy is lying in\nwait around every single corner.
(What's our move? Wait till they arrive?\nNo, we'll never hold out that long.)
(Pull back and regroup, then? No,\nthat leaves Kirsty's crew to hang.\nDammit! This is too much for me!)
Sorry! I'm sorry! But, um, that was also\npart of Kirsty's message—and she was\nvery specific about the yelling.
She had you tell me to ＂pull it together＂?
W-well, she said that if it looked like you\nwere fretting and struggling that I should\ngo ahead and...yell that at you, yes.
She said to forget about your position and\nstandard operating procedure and just...\num...go with your gut?
Because in the end, it's the side with\nthe stronger will that wins! At least...\nthat's what she said.
Pfft! Okay, that is some TERRIBLE advice.\nIn what world does anything EVER work\nlike that?! Aaah ha ha ha!
Well, assuming she's actually serious,\nfiguring out what I WANT to do is easy.
I know you only just got back, Noelle,\nbut I've got a message for you.
Ugh, there's no end to them. They might\ngrind us down with sheer numbers before\nwe can join the main force...
You'd better be alive out there, Joachim!
Joachim?! What are you doing here?\nWho's in command at the battle site?!
I left the prince in charge and ducked out.
Turns out I'm built more for support than\nstanding at the lead doling out orders.
Hey, you're the one who told me to\njust do what my gut told me, right?\nWell, say hello to my gut.
Can you at least assure me there's more\nto your plan than running out here alone?
Course there is! And assuming Noelle\ndelivered the message, there should be\nmovement on that any minute now.
Enemy supply route severed, sir!\nOur dispersed troops are converging\non the rendezvous point as scheduled!
Good work. In that case, let's get this\nlittle counteroffensive rolling!
So you split the force up to make them\nmore agile as a whole, eh?
Small teams move faster than an army.\nPlus, a little bit of sabotage goes a long\nway toward causing serious mayhem.

We give 'em the runaround and stretch the
enemy line thin, then hit them with all our
forces at once at the moment I told Noelle
to relay.
Not bad... So, when do we strike?
Daybreak—which only gives us a few\nhours to clean things up here.
Oh, that's plenty. Hit them fast, decisively,\nand without hesitation. Show the enemy\nhell, and nothing more.
＂Leave no foe with spirit uncrushed,＂\nright? Yeah, I've heard this speech before.\nHow long you think we've been together?
Long enough for me to know you'd\nsee this mission through.
You saying that out of trust in my record,\nor faith based on your expectations of me?
Heh. Guess there's no reason it has\nto be one or the other.
The enemy won't wait around while you\nwax philosophical, Joachim.
Right now, we're off to pierce the center of\nthe enemy formation and take their rear.\nNow come with me if you want to win!
*sigh* She always steals the good lines.
But every time I see her back, I know I'm\ngonna follow it, so maybe that's my own\nexpectations talking.
But enough thinking. I've got work to do.\nAll right, men! Once we split 'em, surround\nthe enemy and attack from all sides!
